Interpol is stepping in to help government finalise the extradition of the Gupta brothers. DA MP and former NPA prosecutor, Glynnis Breytenbach has more on this. Courtesy of #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Time is running out, and the National Prosecuting Authority cannot afford to mess the Gupta case up. That's the warning from former NPA prosecutor, Glynnis Breytenbach. The government, with Interpol, are finalising the extradition of the Gupta brothers. Atul and Rajesh Gupta were arrested in Dubai in June on charges of fraud and corruption. Watch the video above for more details on this story.